25/11/2010
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- The High Court in Podgorica sentenced a Montenegrin member of the notorious Pink Panthers crime gang on Wednesday (November 24th) to eight years in prison. 
Vladimir Lekic was convicted for his involvement in a robbery of a jewellery store in Frankfurt in 2003. 
Lekic and two other people stole jewels and watches worth 2.5m euros. 
He was arrested in Cetinje in June 2009 based on an international arrest warrant issued by Germany. 
His two accomplices are in jail in France. 
Lekic's lawyer vowed to appeal the sentence. 
(RTCG, RTS, AP, AFP - 24/11/10)
